  "text": "Qualitative research [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] has highlighted the views and experiences of patients (e.g. hypertensive, stroke patients) engaging with HBPM. Patients report feeling more empowered and involved in their care [CITATION_5] and more knowledgeable about the risks implicated in high BP [CITATION_6] . HBPM operates to reassure and assists people to reflect on, and regulate aspects of their health management [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] . It is seen as an easy and straightforward technique with which most feel confident [CITATION_10] .",
